page_0:"Mausoleus - Journal
Winter, year of the star 1543.

It is done. Their screams still echo in the stone. I shall miss her in my own way. Why could she not come to love me? Was my commitment not shown in the way I took the head of her petty thief husband? Did I not offer to have her brat daughter looked after by the village spinsters? She could have had everything. No matter, now she will be down here forever, within the stone walls that shall soon be my resting place."